      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "Waste Per Person Peaked in 2000",
        "body": "In the chart below, you'll see that the amount of waste each person produced hit a high in 2000 at 273 kg. From there, it steadily declined. By 2012, each person generated just 173 kg annually. This suggests more mindful disposal and potentially more effective recycling over the years.",
