      },
      {
        "type": "narrative",
        "heading": "Fewer Waste Containers Seen Across the City",
        "body": "In the other chart, notice how the count of waste containers decreased over time. From its peak in 2004 at 47,900, the number dropped significantly, finishing at 37,311 by 2012. This 22% reduction mirrors the efforts to minimize waste production.",
